<p>I have seen some of your photo shoots on the Reddit and i do have a slight concern.</p>
<p>Its like this, i see you taking popular characters and changing elements of their appearance in ways that have me wondering if you are attempting to distinguish your depictions far enough away from the original art/photos so as to put your game into copyright, with a certain level of originality.</p>
<p>Not to own the characters themselves in any significant way, but perhaps just so your games original elements can be something other than the CC 3.0 that pretty much covers 99.999999% of everything SCP in the wiki and across the web.</p>
<p>I apologize if you have clarified this, one way or the other, someplace else.</p>
<p>So the question should be asked: Is your game going to be CC 3.0 and free for anyone to take and rework themselves after your games production/distribution?</p>
<p>Disclaimer: I am developing a game myself, and it will also contain original elements and it will be 100% CC 3.0 for anyone to do whatever they please with after me. Including building their own cards and expansion packs to add to my game.</p>

