			<div class="content" id="post-content-1833277">
									

<p>Just wanted to give a small heads-up on the project, how are we doing so far.</p>
<p>Yesterday, we had a meeting with our team where we finally finished the <strong>Rules of the game</strong>. The rules are quite simple so far, nothing that would require reading several GM books before you'd even start playing. A good rule of thumb, however, is the recommended player count, which is best around 3-5. The recommendation for players being 18 and up also took place. It's not that younger players couldn't play it, but it's simply for the best experience of the game. Also, there are a few nasty &quot;tasks&quot; the player might have to complete during the game.</p>
<p>Also, I wanted to thank all the folks from the SCP wiki for their input so far. Namely, <strong>toadking07, Kyo13 (with help of Defrasa and Fladdledoo), anqxyr, Gears and TroyL</strong> so far. It's always great to join heads together, as we Czechs say, and figure something better out.</p>
<p>As for the content of the game, we already processed around <strong>140 SCPs</strong> into the game. Our goal is around 300-400. We're working on the graphic design, while making the last tweaks to the overall look of the cards. And then, it's betatesting time!</p>
<p>EDIT: Just wanted to add <strong>Barbequedsteak, Reject and GottaGoFeast</strong> into the list of credited folks. My brain sometimes wanders off. Sorry guys!</p>

