			<div class="content" id="post-content-1838571">
									

<p>And on we go.</p>
<p>The rules have surprisingly catched on and don't really need any bigger edits. Might publish them after the betatesting phase. As for the other stuff, we're only tweaking with the difficulty, the playability of the various SCPs adapted into the game, adding some object classes as need be (not inventing a new S/E/K, mind you; by classes I mean tags, like Chemical, Humane, Inhumane&#8230;) and so on. I'd like to credit <strong>LycanTherapy</strong> here, since he agreed with the use of his SCP symbols. Thanks, man.</p>
<p>Got about <strong>160 SCPs</strong> ready for the game already out of the <strong>350 SCP goal.</strong>The adapted SCPs range from less known ones with a few upvotes ( 1092, 1094) to some of the well known ones (173, 231, 012) , both from the first and second series, and so far almost all 001 proposals had been adapted to the game too. We're going to betatest soon and see how it turns out.</p>
<p>Right now, we are <strong>looking for artists with experience in drawing and digital drawing for the card pictures.</strong> There will be pictorial representations of every SCP used and we'd like to refrain from using the pictures already on scp-wiki.<br />
If anybody would like to help out in this manner - please send me a PM. We have cookies!</p>

